<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4860> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4860" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The author of an agrarian bill in which he proposed to set up a commission of ten, elected for five years with imperium, to found colonies and assign public lands in Italy and the provinces, and to use booty and public funds for the purchase of land (Cic. Leg. Agr. I, II, and III, passim; Rab. Perd. 32; Att. 2.1.3; Sull. 65; Pis. 4; Plin. NH 7.117; 8.210; Plut. Cic. 12.2-5; Dio 37.25.4). The bill was successfully opposed by Cicero and threatened with a veto by Caecilius (Cic.Sull.65)." .
